attachments.title: Ricardo Semler: How to run a company with (almost) no rules
attachments.text: What if your job didn’t control your life? Brazilian CEO Ricardo Semler practices a radical form of corporate democracy, rethinking everything from board meetings to how workers report their vacation days (they don’t have to). It’s a vision that rewards the wisdom of workers, promotes work-life balance — and leads to some deep insight on what work, and life, is really all about. Bonus question: What if schools were like this too?

Hi all - Some of you who have applied to the Immersive program have been asking about when you get access to the precourse work… you will get an on-boarding email from Amy Saylor or Galvanize exactly 32 days before the program starts. You will need to respond with your GitHub account. If you aren’t already set up on GitHub, you’ll need to do that. The pre-course work takes about 20-40 hours to complete. It’s basically a warm up of HTML, CSS and jQuery… all things you have been doing already. Hope this helps and let me know if you have questions! :smiley:

Hey guys, we'll be using some images for the in-class project today. Try to think of something of a subject you can grab images of. You can use your own photos or just use whatever you find in a google search. A few subjects off the top of my head:

Your favorite car
Your family
A trip you took
Different types of food from around the world
Dogs (cats just aren't as cool)
Screenshots from video games
Weird Google earth images
Different beers or the beer making process
Characters from a TV show
Cool homes from around the world
Candy
General photography

Just try to have some kind of subject in mind so you can collect 8-12 images relating to each other. Thanks!
